We have derived an analytic expression to compute the outcome of PrediXcan using only summary statistics from genetic association studies. Details of the derivation are shown in the Methods section. In Fig. 1a we illustrate the mechanics of Summary-PrediXcan (S-PrediXcan) in relation to traditional GWAS and the individual-level PrediXcan method11.Fig. 1
Comparison between GWAS, PrediXcan, and S-PrediXcan. a Compares GWAS, PrediXcan, and Summary-PrediXcan. Both GWAS and PrediXcan take genotype and phenotype data as input. GWAS computes the regression coefficients of Y on Xl using the model \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
